## 1. Purpose
This document defines the security and privacy roles within [COMPANY], their responsibilities, and their decision authority, so that accountability for the ISMS is explicit and unambiguous. It satisfies the HIPAA requirement to designate a Security Officer and a Privacy Officer, and provides the authoritative role definitions referenced by every other policy in the set.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all workforce members (employees, contractors, interns, temporary staff) and to all roles that own, operate, or oversee in-scope systems and data per `isms-scope-statement.md.template`. Roles are functional; one individual may hold several roles, and a role may be shared, provided accountability remains clear.

## 3. Policy
1. [COMPANY] **shall** designate, in writing, a HIPAA Security Officer and a HIPAA Privacy Officer, identified by name and kept current.
2. Every security responsibility in the ISMS **shall** map to an accountable role defined in this document.
3. Roles **shall** observe separation of duties where practical; where segregation is not feasible due to size, compensating controls and oversight **shall** be documented.
4. Role assignments **shall** be reviewed at least annually and upon organizational change, and reflected here and in access entitlements.
5. All workforce members **shall** understand and acknowledge the responsibilities applicable to their role as part of onboarding and annual training.

## 4. Role Definitions

### 4.1 Executive Sponsor / [CEO / Board]
Accountable for the security program; owns the apex Information Security Policy; provides budget, staffing, and authority; accepts residual risk on behalf of the organization; chairs or sponsors the Security Steering Committee.

### 4.2 HIPAA Security Officer / [CISO]
The designated Security Officer under 45 CFR § 164.308(a)(2). Owns and operates the ISMS, the policy set, the risk program, and technical/administrative safeguards for ePHI. Reports security posture and risk to leadership and the steering committee.

### 4.3 HIPAA Privacy Officer
The designated Privacy Officer under 45 CFR § 164.530(a)(1). Owns privacy policies, the Notice of Privacy Practices, individual rights, minimum-necessary determinations, and leads breach determinations per `../healthcare/hipaa-breach-notification-procedure.md.template`.

### 4.4 Security Steering Committee
Cross-functional governance body that sets security priorities, reviews risk, and approves major decisions. Defined in `security-steering-committee-charter.md.template`.

### 4.5 Compliance / Audit Lead
Owns the HITRUST/SOC 2 assessment lifecycle, MyCSF, the Statement of Applicability, the internal audit program, and corrective-action tracking. May be the Security Officer in a small org.

### 4.6 Engineering / Platform Leads
Accountable for secure design, build, and operation of in-scope [AWS], [Snowflake], and [GitHub] systems; implement and evidence technical controls; act as control owners.

### 4.7 System / Control Owners
Named owners of specific systems or controls; maintain configuration, access, monitoring, and evidence for their area; keep their SoA entries accurate.

### 4.8 People / HR
Owns onboarding/offboarding, background checks, the sanctions process, and ensuring training completion; partners on workforce-related controls.

### 4.9 Legal / Counsel
Confirms legal and regulatory obligations, reviews BAAs and breach notifications, and advises on state-law overlays.

### 4.10 All Workforce Members
Comply with all applicable policies; complete required training; protect credentials and PHI; report security incidents and suspected breaches promptly.

